results.overview:
Magnet schools are public school options that provide a school-wide curriculum designed around a specific theme. They are intended to attract a diverse pool of applicants and historically have accommodated students from outside their zone or district. While some schools may have the word "magnet" in their school's name, only a school that currently gets Magnet Schools Assistance Program (M.S.A.P) funding is labeled as a "magnet school" on it's MySchools page. This magnet school offers a school-wide curriculum around the theme of Environmental Studies and Community Wellness. Nestled in the vibrant community of Coney Island, Brooklyn, PS 90 is a dedicated Magnet School focused on Environmental Studies and Community Wellness. Our mission is to cultivate a generation of environmentally conscious learners equipped with the knowledge, skills, and passion to make a positive impact on their communities and the world.

At PS 90, we believe that education goes beyond the classroom. We strive to create an engaging, hands-on learning environment where students can explore the interconnections between the environment, health, and social responsibility. Our curriculum emphasizes sustainability, promoting awareness of environmental issues while encouraging students to adopt healthy lifestyle choices.

Students engage in experiential learning through outdoor explorations, field trips, and community projects that foster a deep understanding of ecosystems, conservation, and climate change. We prioritize physical and mental wellness through programs that include nutrition, fitness, and social-emotional learning, empowering students to lead balanced lives. Our school fosters strong ties with local organizations, allowing students to participate in community service projects and initiatives that promote environmental stewardship and social equity.

We utilize project-based learning and interdisciplinary approaches to make education relevant and inspiring. Students collaborate on real-world challenges, developing critical thinking, creativity, and problem-solving skills. Our dedicated faculty is committed to creating a supportive and inclusive atmosphere where every student can thrive.

As we work toward a greener, healthier future, PS 90 remains focused on empowering the next generation of leaders to advocate for environmental sustainability and community wellness. For more information about enrollment, programs, and events, please explore our website or contact us directly.
